data.text:
At least 65 Russian soldiers killed in Ukraine missile strikes as they lined up in field for a general's inspection

The commander for whom the Russian troops had been lined up never arrived for the inspection.

Russian military suffered at least 4,000 casualties in battle for Ukraine city

Ukraine Defense Minister Rustem Umerov said at least 4,000 Russian troops had been killed in Moscow's attempt to seize control of Avdiivka.

Ukraine bans civilians from 'post-apocalyptic' front-line city over constant Russian missile, rocket attacks

The city of Avdiivka in the Donetsk region has been bombarded by Russian rockets.

Remnants of Russian platoon refuse to fight after 'bulls--t' mobilization to Donbas

A viral video shows a Russian officer in eastern Ukraine saying that he and his men are refusing to carry out orders.

Russian soldiers dying at highest rate since beginning of war with more than 800 daily

The rate of 824 deaths per day is about four times higher than the average was in June-July 2022, the UK gov said.

Putin 'supplied' Buk missile that shot down Flight MH17 over Ukraine: investigators

International prosecutors found that evidence of Vladimir Putin's involvement was not concrete enough to secure a criminal conviction.

Russia warns it will 'gain world's attention' on 1st anniversary of Ukraine war

Ukrainian officials and Western analysts believe Russia is getting ready to launch a massive new offensive in the east, which could involve up to 500,000 troops.

Ukraine braces for Russian offensive in Luhansk ahead of war anniversary

Russia is said to be planning a major offensive to try and break the impasse on the battlefield ahead of the Feb. 24 anniversary of the invasion.

Putin preparing to mobilize more than 200,000 new troops to Ukraine, NATO chief warns

NATO Secretary-General Jens Stoltenberg said there is "no sign" that the warmongering leader is "preparing for peace."

Russians are trying to advance in Bakhmut over own soldiers' corpses: Ukraine

Gen. Valerii Zaluzhnyi wrote on his Facebook page Tuesday that there was intense fighting along the border of Svatove-Kreminna in the Luhansk region, as well as in the direction of Lysychansk.

Russian ex-deputy PM wounded in Ukrainian shelling of Donbas hotel

Dmitry Rogozin was having a business lunch at a hotel restaurant in Donetsk when the venue was shelled by high-precision weapons.
